10 killed after train collides with bus in China
At least ten people were killed and eleven others injured today after a passenger bus and a cargo train collided in northeast China Province.The collision took place this morning at a railway crossing in Heihe City of Heilongjiang province, state-runXinhua news agency reported.The accident happened when a supervisor in charge of the railway crossing failed to reach the area in time to warn vehicles of the approaching train at a railway crossing in Heihe City, a senior railway official in Heihe told Xinhua.All the victims were passengers on the bus, which belonged to a local public transport company while the train, operated by a local railway company in Heihe, has left the scene. The railway line resumed operation, the report said.